s mattered a great deal in how they fared after the war.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jan 2021) 0aChild soldierszLiberia. 0aVeteran reintegrationzLiberia. 0aYoung menzLiberiaxSocial conditionsy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017z978311066609040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813573502zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813573502zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813573502.jpg  a978-3-11-066609-0 RUP eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA